BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ltjufVWQB4tXFph_HdQhe
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260321T224053Z
DTSTART:20260322T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-03-22T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-03-22T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sA-2RgSDPsCDyVf0UVg0A
SUMMARY:Susan Meiselas: Crossings
DTSTAMP:20260321T224053Z
DTSTART:20260322T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:First presented at the Art Institute of Chicago in 1990\, this 
	exhibition by Susan Meiselas intertwines documentary photographs of Centra
	l America during the 1970s and 1980s \\(from Nicaragua and El Salvador\\) 
	along with panoramic images from the US/Mexico border taken in 1989. Addit
	ional photographs of the US/Mexico border taken in 2018 are also featured 
	in a site-specific gallery installation. The exhibition invites viewers to
	 see immigration in the context of economic and political crises in the re
	gion.\n\nToday\, the work feels newly urgent. US immigration enforcement h
	as expanded through militarization and constant surveillance\, with leader
	s using fear-driven language to divide communities and legitimize brutal f
	orms of control.\n\nThese photographs ask us to look carefully\, to recogn
	ize familiar patterns\, and to hold on to our shared humanity across the g
	lobe. People move in search of safety\, possibility\, and a better life fo
	r their families\, which is a universal hope that crosses borders\, genera
	tions\, and time.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/susan-m
	eiselas-crossings/17977024/2026-03-22T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/susan-meiselas-crossings/
	17977024/2026-03-22T00
LOCATION:Photographic Center Northwest (PCNW)\, 900 12th Ave.\, Seattle\, W
	A
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:qXSkMEtewLNSxu1PB6h4I
SUMMARY:CROSSROADS BELLEVUE INVITES COMMUNITY TO ‘LIVE MUSIC AT THE MARKET 
	STAGE
DTSTAMP:20260321T224053Z
DTSTART:20260322T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Crossroads Bellevue\, a one-of-a-kind shopping\, dining\, and e
	ntertainment destination in the heart of Bellevue\, Washington \\(https://
	crossroadsbellevue.com\\)\, invites the community to enjoy “Live Music at 
	the Market Stage\,” a series of free live musical performances held in the
	 public market every Friday \\(7 p.m. to 8:45 p.m.\\)\, Saturday \\(7 p.m.
	 to 8:45 p.m.\\)\, and Sunday \\(12:30 p.m. to 2:30 p.m.\\) now through th
	e end of the year. Performances include an eclectic mix of acoustic guitar
	\, Cuban music\, jazz\, local choirs and more. All performances are free o
	f charge. To learn more about each upcoming performance\, visit Market Sta
	ge | Crossroads Bellevue. While enjoying the music\, guests are encouraged
	 to dine at one of the center’s many restaurants. For more information abo
	ut Crossroads Bellevue\, visit https://crossroadsbellevue.com.\n\nWHEN:   
	          Each Friday\, Saturday and Sunday through the End of the Year\n\
	n-        Fridays: 7 p.m. - 8:45 p.m.\n\n-        Saturdays: 7 p.m. - 8:45
	 p.m.\n\n-        Sundays: 12:30 p.m. - 2:30 p.m.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amc
